snippet.textDisplay:
If I would rank all big Arrowverse crossover events it would be like this:
1. Crisis on Earth-X. The only major crossover that featured more than 2 shows that didn't dissappoint me in some way.
2. Worlds Finest. Kara and Barry's interactions is what make this episode so great, Melissa and Grant have such amasing chemsitry
3. Crisis on Infinite Earths. An amasing spectacle in many ways but this crossover also had some serious flaws.
4. Flash vs Arrow. The first big crossover event was really fun.
5. Elseworld. Pretty forgetable, I barely remember anything from it.
6. Invasion. The plot was a mess, the Dominators were not good villains, the Arrow episode felt really out of place and ruined the pacing.
7. Heroes Join Forces. Vandal Savage was such a a bad villain and the hawk people sucked aswell (two of the biggest reasons why the first season of Legends also was pretty terrible)
8. Duet. I just hate musical episodes

snippet.textDisplay: As much as I enjoyed this scene "beginning of Justice League", my problem with this scene is this. No matter which show I watch, Batwoman, Supergirl, Flash, etc... any "big villain" that they are facing in their respective shows I can't help but think the reduced amount of danger now. To explain this, anyone of those other heroes can simply step in and lend an assist or replace the hero should the hero fall. In addition, I would also be thinking that while the said hero is struggling, I would be thinking how easily the other heroes would be able to resolve it. Those are my thoughts on this crossover.
